13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-126 of Title 70, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. As used in this section:
18 1. “Bell to bell” means the time between the first bell ringing
19 at the start of the school day to begin instructional time until the
20 dismissal bell at the end of the school day to end instructional
21 time; and
22 2. “Personal electronic device” means a personal device capable
23 of connecting to a smart phone, the Internet, or a cellular or Wi-Fi
24 network, or directly connecting to another similar device. Personal
