1 elec tronic devices include, but are not limited to, smart watches,
2 smart headphones, laptops, tablets, and smart glasses. Personal
3 electronic devices shall not include school-issued or school-
4 approved devices that are specifically limited for use in classroom
5 instruction.
6 B. Each school district board of education shall adopt a policy
7 prohibiting students from using cell phones and personal electronic
8 devices while on the campus of a public school district from bell to
9 bell. The policy shall include disciplinary procedures for
10 violations.
11 C. The policy adopted pursuant to subsection B of this section
12 may provide for exceptions including, but not limited to:
13 1. Emergency use of cell phones or personal electronic devices
14 by students during the school day; and
15 2. Use of cell phones or personal electronic devices by
16 students who use them to monitor health issues.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
18 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
19 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
21 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
